    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSometimes message chunks passed to `vim.ui_attach` callback have lost some whitespace characters compared to the built-in UI appearance. \n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8e13b594-f70b-40e7-9bf9-61423b37a37e)\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`init.lua`:\n```lua\nlocal api = vim.api\nlocal ns = api.nvim_create_namespace('messageRedirection')\n\nlocal function log(msg)\n  api.nvim_buf_set_lines(1, -1, -1, true, vim.split(msg, '\\n'))\n  vim.cmd.normal 'G'\nend\n\nlocal function detach()\n  api.nvim__redraw({flush = true})\n  vim.ui_detach(ns)\n  api.nvim__redraw({flush = true})\nend\n\napi.nvim_create_autocmd('CmdlineEnter', {callback = detach})\n\nlocal redirect = true\n\nlocal function attach()\n  if not redirect then\n    return\n  end\n  api.nvim__redraw({flush = true})\n  vim.ui_attach(ns, {ext_messages = true, ext_cmdline = false}, function (event, _, content, _)\n    if event ~= 'msg_show' then\n      return\n    end\n\n    vim.schedule(function ()\n      log(vim.inspect(content))\n      api.nvim__redraw({flush = true})\n    end)\n  end)\nend\n\napi.nvim_create_autocmd({'CmdlineLeave'}, {callback = attach})\n\napi.nvim_create_autocmd({'UIEnter'}, {\n  callback = attach\n})\n\napi.nvim_create_user_command('MsgRedirToggle', function ()\n  redirect = not redirect\n  if not redirect then\n    detach()\n  end\nend, {nargs = 0})\n```\n- `nvim --clean -u init.lua`\n- enter `:filter Search hi` command\n- enter `:MsgRedirToggle`\n- enter `:filter Search hi` command again and compare results, especially look at the chunk contents before `xxx`. I get\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/09b523f9-d181-4c45-89e8-f2767d645e7b)\n\nOnly the first line has any space before `xxx`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhitespace characters are preserved in ui_attach callback. \n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.0-dev-1380+g7121983c45\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom repo",
